  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Additionally, AI systems can analyze speech samples, facial movements, and imaging data to detect patterns indicative of specific impairments.",
    "Research shows such growing usefulness of AI.",
    "Automated clustering of connected speech has distinguished aphasia subtypes (Fromm et al., 2022; Rezaii et al., 2024), ASR systems have helped identify Parkinson's disease (Crawford, 2025; Escobar-Grisales et al., 2023), and AI-assisted picture description analyses have shown promise for Alzheimer's detection (Agbavor & Liang, 2022).",
    "Videofluoroscopic swallowing studies have also benefited from automated aspiration detection (Iida et al., 2023).",
    "Beyond diagnosis, AI can predict treatment outcomes by synthesizing demographic, behavioral, and neuroimaging data (Billot et al., 2022), and some day, AI may simulate responses to interventions particularly for bilingual individuals."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Automated clustering of connected speech has distinguished aphasia subtypes (Fromm et al., 2022; Rezaii et al., 2024), ASR systems have helped identify Parkinson's disease (Crawford, 2025; Escobar-Grisales et al., 2023), and AI-assisted picture description analyses have shown promise for Alzheimer's detection (Agbavor & Liang, 2022).",
    "Videofluoroscopic swallowing studies have also benefited from automated aspiration detection (Iida et al., 2023).",
